'''Anonym.OS''' was a [[LiveCD]] [[operating system]] based on [[OpenBSD]] 3.8 with strong [[encryption]] and anonymization tools. The goal of the project was to provide a secure anonymous [[internet|web browsing]] access to everyday users. '''Anonym.OS''' was a [[Live CD]] [[operating system]] based on [[OpenBSD]] 3.8 with strong [[encryption]] and anonymization tools. The goal of the project was to provide a secure anonymous [[internet|web browsing]] access to everyday users. The operating system was [[OpenBSD]] 3.8, although many [[Software package|packages]] have been added to facilitate its goal. It used [[Fluxbox]] as its [[window manager]].
